Cuomo Announces Veto of New York School Pension-Borrowing Legislation

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-07-13T15:47:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/cuomo-announces-veto-of-new-york-school-pension-borrowing-legislation.html
New York  Governor Andrew M. Cuomo
vetoed a measure that would have allowed school districts to
borrow more than $1 billion through bonds to cover current
pension costs, according to an e-mailed statement.  “New York has no future as the tax capital of the
nation,” Cuomo said in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  